    "domain_description": "The UKMLA Applied Knowledge Test (AKT) assesses the knowledge and understanding required for safe practice as a newly qualified UK doctor. It covers clinical sciences, professional practice, and system-based clinical medicine across all major specialties. The exam emphasizes clinical application, patient safety, evidence-based practice, and professional standards as defined by the GMC's Outcomes for Graduates and the UK Foundation Programme Curriculum. Questions test integration of basic sciences with clinical scenarios, diagnostic reasoning, management planning, and professional judgment.",
